</div></fieldset><fieldset class="optin-options">
    <legend>Can we stay in touch?</legend>
    <ul>
        <li>
            <input class="lp-radio" type="radio" name="opt_in" id="optin-yes" value="1">
            <label class="lp-radio-label" for="optin-yes">Yes. Send me emails with ways that I can support Wikipedia.</label>
        </li>
        <li>
            <input class="lp-radio" type="radio" name="opt_in" id="optin-no" value="0">
            <label class="lp-radio-label" for="optin-no">No. Don't send me an occasional email with opportunities to support Wikipedia.</label>
        </li>
    </ul>
    <div class="optin-no-prompt" data-is-translated="yes">
        <div class="optin-no-prompt__no">Sorry to hear that. We don't email often; would you consider changing your mind?</div>
        <div class="optin-no-prompt__yes">Thanks for changing your mind! We'll respect your inbox.</div>
    </div>
    <div id="error-optin" class="lp-error" style="display: none;" tabindex="-1"><!-- tabindex="-1" allows focus with js so it can be announced -->
        Please select an email option
    </div>
    <div class="optin-smallprint links-in-new-tab">
        The Wikimedia Foundation will send you email updates and tell you if Wikipedia needs your support or advice in the future. Your information is handled in accordance with our <a class="external text" href="https://foundation.wikimedia.org/wiki/Donor_privacy_policy" target="_blank">donor privacy policy</a>. Each email you receive will include easy unsubscribe options.
    </div>
</fieldset>


